race.comment: GENRICHERO (2) is down seriously in grade on last start, when he started single-figure odds and was beaten only 1.25 lengths by Black Run, who is a leading contender for Saturday's Pakenham Cup. Not beaten too far by the same horse the start prior and that looks the standout form reference for this. HOT TOO GO (3) beat GENRICHERO home two back and probably needs to be forgiven the poor last start because three runs ago he also defeated AMLETO (1), who's a key player here. He's probably got a little improvement to come than GENRICHERO and HOT TOO GO and tuned up for this with a nice recent trial win. RELIABLE JO (8) is deep into the first prep now, but wasn't far off LEONCHROI last start so if he can hold that form for one more run he could play a role.
